#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:2
msgid "EnvVars"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:6
msgid ""
"These tools are still **experimental** (so subject to breaking changes) but "
"with very stable syntax. We encourage the usage of it to be prepared for "
"Conan 2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:10
msgid ""
"``EnvVars`` is a class that represents an instance of environment variables "
"for a given system. It is obtained from the generic ``Environment`` class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:13
msgid ""
"This class is used by other tools like the :ref:`conan.tools."
"gnu<conan_tools_gnu>` autotools helpers and the :ref:"
"`VirtualBuildEnv<conan_tools_env_virtualbuildenv>` and :ref:"
"`VirtualRunEnv<conan_tools_env_virtualrunenv>` generator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:19
msgid "Creating environment files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:21
msgid ""
"``EnvVars`` object can generate environment (shell, bat or powershell "
"scripts) files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:31
msgid ""
"def generate(self):\n"
"    env1 = Environment()\n"
"    env1.define(\"foo\", \"var\")\n"
"    envvars = env1.vars(self)\n"
"    envvars.save_script(\"my_env_file\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:32
msgid ""
"Although it potentially could be used in other methods, this functionality "
"is intended to work in the ``generate()`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:35
msgid ""
"It will generate automatically a ``my_env_file.bat`` for Windows systems or "
"``my_env_file.sh`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:37
msgid ""
"In Windows, it is possible to opt-in to generate Powershell ``.ps1`` scripts "
"instead of ``.bat`` ones, using the conf ``tools.env.virtualenv:"
"powershell=True``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:40
msgid ""
"Also, by default, Conan will automatically append that launcher file path to "
"a list that will be used to create a ``conanbuild.bat|sh|ps1`` file "
"aggregating all the launchers in order. The ``conanbuild.sh|bat|ps1`` "
"launcher will be created after the execution of the ``generate()`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:44
msgid ""
"The ``scope`` argument (``\"build\"`` by default) can be used to define "
"different scope of environment files, to aggregate them separately. For "
"example, using a ``scope=\"run\"``, like the ``VirtualRunEnv`` generator "
"does, will aggregate and create a ``conanrun.bat|sh|ps1`` script:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:57
msgid ""
"def generate(self):\n"
"    env1 = Environment(self)\n"
"    env1.define(\"foo\", \"var\")\n"
"    envvars = env1.vars(self, scope=\"run\")\n"
"    # Will append \"my_env_file\" to \"conanrun.bat|sh|ps1\"\n"
"    envvars.save_script(\"my_env_file\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:58
msgid ""
"You can also use ``scope=None`` argument to avoid appending the script to "
"the aggregated ``conanbuild.bat|sh|ps1``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:68
msgid ""
"env1 = Environment(self)\n"
"env1.define(\"foo\", \"var\")\n"
"# Will not append \"my_env_file\" to \"conanbuild.bat|sh|ps1\"\n"
"envvars = env1.vars(self, scope=None)\n"
"envvars.save_script(\"my_env_file\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:70
msgid "Running with environment files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:72
msgid ""
"The ``conanbuild.bat|sh|ps1`` launcher will be executed by default before "
"calling every ``self.run()`` command. This would be typically done in the "
"``build()`` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:75
msgid ""
"You can change the default launcher with the ``env`` argument of ``self."
"run()``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:87
msgid ""
"...\n"
"def build(self):\n"
"    # This will automatically wrap the \"foo\" command with the correct "
"environment:\n"
"    # source my_env_file.sh && foo\n"
"    # my_env_file.bat && foo\n"
"    # powershell my_env_file.ps1 ; cmd c/ foo\n"
"    self.run(\"foo\", env=[\"my_env_file\"])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:89
msgid "Applying the environment variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:91
msgid ""
"As an alternative to running a command, environments can be applied in the "
"python environment:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:103
msgid ""
"from conan.tools.env import Environment\n"
"\n"
"env1 = Environment(self)\n"
"env1.define(\"foo\", \"var\")\n"
"envvars = env1.vars(self)\n"
"with envvars.apply():\n"
"   # Here os.getenv(\"foo\") == \"var\"\n"
"   ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:105
msgid "Iterating the variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:107
msgid ""
"You can iterate the environment variables of an ``EnvVars`` object like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:119
msgid ""
"env1 = Environment()\n"
"env1.append(\"foo\", \"var\")\n"
"env1.append(\"foo\", \"var2\")\n"
"envvars = env1.vars(self)\n"
"for name, value in envvars.items():\n"
"    assert name == \"foo\":\n"
"    assert value == \"var var2\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/conanfile/tools/env/envvars.rst:122
msgid ""
